# SQLSTATE Error Handling

All user-facing errors in RQDB must use `Error::Sql { state, message }` with
a proper `SqlState` variant — never `Error::Catalog(...)` for conditions that
a SQL user can trigger.

## Rules

- **Every new error condition needs a SQLSTATE code.** Before returning an
  error from the executor, db.rs, or any SQL-facing path, check if an
  existing `SqlState` variant fits. If not, add a new one with its ANSI/DB2/
  PostgreSQL code and document it in `src/sql/README.md`.
- **`Error::Catalog` is for internal catalog inconsistencies only** — things
  like a missing system table or corrupt bootstrap data that the user cannot
  cause through SQL.
- **`Error::Io` and `Error::Corruption` stay for infrastructure errors** — disk
  failures, checksum mismatches, etc.
- **Use `sql_error()` helper** — never construct `Error::Sql { .. }` directly.
  The helper in `src/error.rs` ensures consistent formatting.
- **Integration tests for every SQLSTATE** — each reachable code must have at
  least one end-to-end test in `tests/integration.rs` that asserts the
  specific SQLSTATE string (e.g. `"42S02"`, `"54010"`).
- **Document in `src/sql/README.md`** — the SQLSTATE table must list every
  implemented code with its meaning and an example trigger.

## Code Reference

```rust
// ✅ Correct — use sql_error with a specific SqlState
use crate::error::{sql_error, SqlState};
return Err(sql_error(SqlState::TableNotFound, format!("table {} not found", name)));

// ❌ Wrong — generic Catalog error for a user-triggerable condition
return Err(Error::Catalog(format!("table {} not found", name)));
```

## Existing Codes (src/error.rs)

| Code  | Variant               | Meaning                          |
|-------|-----------------------|----------------------------------|
| 42000 | SyntaxError           | Syntax / access rule violation   |
| 42S02 | TableNotFound         | Table not found                  |
| 42S22 | ColumnNotFound        | Column not found                 |
| 42601 | ParseError            | SQL parse error                  |
| 42S01 | TableAlreadyExists    | Table already exists             |
| 42711 | DuplicateColumnName   | Duplicate column in CREATE TABLE |
| 42611 | InvalidColumnLength   | Invalid CHAR/VARCHAR length      |
| 42508 | SystemSchemaViolation | Create/drop in system schema     |
| 42P04 | DatabaseAlreadyExists | Database already exists           |
| 3D000 | DatabaseNotFound      | Database not found               |
| 54010 | RowTooLarge           | Row exceeds page payload         |
| 54011 | TooManyColumns        | Column count exceeds limit       |
| 21S01 | InsertValueListMismatch | Value count ≠ column count     |
| 22000 | DataException         | Unsupported literal type         |
| 22005 | AssignmentError       | Type mismatch in assignment      |
| 23502 | NotNullViolation      | NULL in NOT NULL column          |
| 0A000 | FeatureNotSupported   | Unsupported SQL feature          |
